{
  "texts": [
    "The results are illustrated in Fig. 4.",
    "We found that more positive valence and higher density were associated with higher popularity.",
    "The effect of density (d = 0.21) was twice as large as the effect of valence (d = 0.12); however, both effects were small in magnitude.",
    "High popularity was also associated with long duration (d = 0.32), high readability (d = 0.20), and one topic, Mind.",
    "In contrast, Environment and Society were associated with low popularity."
  ]
}